senses.sense: The 7<sup>th</sup> letter of the English alphabet, called gee and written in the Latin script.
The ordinal number 7<sup>th</sup>, derived from this letter of the English alphabet, called gee and written in the Latin script.
(chiefly US) Abbreviation of grand ("thousand (dollars, pounds etc.)").
(Internet slang) Abbreviation of grin; often enclosed in :* * or < > to indicate that the user is grinning.
(stenoscript) Abbreviation of go and inflections goes, going, gone
